avRtpMib.name: avRtpMib
avRtpMib.contactinfo: Avaya Customer Services Postal: Avaya, Inc. 211 Mt Airy Rd. Basking Ridge, NJ 07920 USA Tel: +1 908 953 6000 WWW: http://www.avaya.com
avRtpMib.description: This module defines an interface to RTP sessions QoS statistic gathering capabilities in Avaya's VoIP enabled devices. The MIB, designed for Avaya Services, allows operators to perform the following tasks: 1. View the statistics of recently terminated RTP session. 2. Define QoS related thresholds that define bad-QoS conditions. 3. View the statistics of last session, which experienced bad QoS. 4. Enable a special QoS trap that is sent upon termination of RTP session with bad QoS. 5. Enable a special QoS fault trap that is sent when more than N streams suffer from bad QoS. And a QoS clear trap that is sent when this fault conditions ends. 6. Configure the above traps rate limiting mechanism. AvRtpItuPerceivedSeverity.name: AvRtpItuPerceivedSeverity
AvRtpItuPerceivedSeverity.reference: ITU Recommendation M.3100, 'Generic Network Information Model', 1995 ITU Recommendation X.733, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: Alarm Reporting Function', 1992

AvRtpSilenceSupp.name: AvRtpSilenceSupp
AvRtpSilenceSupp.description: Silence Suppression modes where: noRtp(2) No RTP packets during silence periods SilenceFrames(3) The codec sends special silence frames during silence periods Complex(4) A combination of the above

avRtpQoSTrap.name: avRtpQoSTrap
avRtpQoSTrap.description: The trap contains QoS statistics for a single RTP session. The device can send this trap when an RTP session that experienced bad QoS terminates

avRtpQoSFault.name: avRtpQoSFault
avRtpQoSFault.description: The trap indicates that more than XXX RTP sessions currently suffers from bad QoS.

avRtpQoSClear.name: avRtpQoSClear
avRtpQoSClear.description: This trap indicates that a QoS fault, previously indicated by an avRtpQoSFault has cleared.

avRtpThresholdEntry.name: avRtpThresholdEntry
avRtpThresholdEntry.description: Each entry contains one set of thresholds. In this version only one entry is supported (1).

avRtpThresholdMinStatWin.name: avRtpThresholdMinStatWin
avRtpThresholdMinStatWin.description: The minimum number of observed RTP sequence numbers advance needed for the evaluation of packet loss.

avRtpThresholdRxCodecLoss.name: avRtpThresholdRxCodecLoss
avRtpThresholdRxCodecLoss.description: Codec packet loss i.e. the loss at the codec decoder. This threshold is evaluated once for each statistical interval (6-12 seconds)

avRtpThresholdRxAvgCodecLoss.name: avRtpThresholdRxAvgCodecLoss
avRtpThresholdRxAvgCodecLoss.description: Threshold on the avarage codec loss

avRtpThresholdRxCodecLossEv.name: avRtpThresholdRxCodecLossEv
avRtpThresholdRxCodecLossEv.description: The device generates a QoS traps if avRtpThresholdRxCodecLoss was crossed avRtpThresholdRxCodecLossEv times during the session (0 means that no traps are sent for this threshold).

avRtpThresholdCodecRtt.name: avRtpThresholdCodecRtt
avRtpThresholdCodecRtt.description: Codec round trip time threshold (an estimate for the overall RTT, including the internal delays). This threshold is evaluated each time an RTCP message is received (usually every 6-12 seconds)

avRtpThresholdCodecRttEv.name: avRtpThresholdCodecRttEv
avRtpThresholdCodecRttEv.description: The device generates a QoS traps if avRtpThresholdCodecRtt was crossed avRtpThresholdCodecRttEv times during the session (0 means that no traps are sent for this threshold).

avRtpThresholdEcReturnLoss.name: avRtpThresholdEcReturnLoss
avRtpThresholdEcReturnLoss.description: Echo Cancellation return loss in -dBm. High value (low absolute) means that a lot of energy is returned which can result in auditable echos. This threshold is evaluated once for each statistical interval (6-12 seconds)

avRtpThresholdRxLoss.name: avRtpThresholdRxLoss
avRtpThresholdRxLoss.description: The received packet loss. This threshold is evaluated once for each statistical interval (6-12 seconds)

avRtpThresholdRxLossEv.name: avRtpThresholdRxLossEv
avRtpThresholdRxLossEv.description: The device generates a QoS traps if avRtpThresholdRxCodecLoss was crossed avRtpThresholdRxCodecLossEv times during the session (0 means that no traps are sent for this threshold).

avRtpThresholdRemLoss.name: avRtpThresholdRemLoss
avRtpThresholdRemLoss.description: Remote peer packet loss threshold learnt from received RTCP reports. This threshold is evaluated once for each statistical interval (6-12 seconds)

avRtpThresholdAvgRxLoss.name: avRtpThresholdAvgRxLoss
avRtpThresholdAvgRxLoss.description: The received average packet loss. This threshold is evaluated at the end of the session.

avRtpThresholdAvgRemLoss.name: avRtpThresholdAvgRemLoss
avRtpThresholdAvgRemLoss.description: Threshold on the average remote packet loss, learnt from RTCP reports. This threshold is evaluated at the end of the session.

avRtpThresholdRxJitter.name: avRtpThresholdRxJitter
avRtpThresholdRxJitter.description: A threshold on the received inter-arrival jitter, measured in milliseconds. This threshold is evaluated once for each statistical interval (6-12 seconds)

avRtpThresholdRemJitter.name: avRtpThresholdRemJitter
avRtpThresholdRemJitter.description: A threshold on the remote inter-arrival jitter, learnt from RTCP reports. This item is measured in milliseconds and is evaluated upon reception of an RTCP message.

avRtpThresholdRtt.name: avRtpThresholdRtt
avRtpThresholdRtt.description: A threshold on the network round-trip-time, measured in milliseconds. This item is evaluated upon reception of RTCP messages.

avRtpThresholdRxSsrcChangeEv.name: avRtpThresholdRxSsrcChangeEv
avRtpThresholdRxSsrcChangeEv.description: The device would generate an end-of-session QoS trap if the number of observed SSRC changes was over this treshold.

avRtpEnable.name: avRtpEnable
avRtpEnable.description: Enable RTP statistic collection by the device. Note that statistic collection may cause minor performance hit.

avRtpQoSFaultTh.name: avRtpQoSFaultTh
avRtpQoSFaultTh.description: The number of concurrent active RTP sessions that suffers from bad QoS (according to avRtpThresholds) that cause the device to enter a 'QoS fault' state. Note, upon entering this fault state, the device sends a avRtpQoSFault trap.

avRtpQoSClearTh.name: avRtpQoSClearTh
avRtpQoSClearTh.description: The number of concurrent active RTP sessions that suffers from bad QoS (according to avRtpThresholds) that clears the 'QoS fault' state. Note, when the QoS fault clears, the device send a avRtpQoSClear trap.

avRtpTxQoSTraps.name: avRtpTxQoSTraps
avRtpTxQoSTraps.description: The number of avRtpQoSTrap sent so far.

avRtpQoSTrapsDrop.name: avRtpQoSTrapsDrop
avRtpQoSTrapsDrop.description: The number of avRtpQoSTraps that were dropped by the rate limiter

avRtpQoSTrapTokenInterval.name: avRtpQoSTrapTokenInterval
avRtpQoSTrapTokenInterval.description: Configure the QoS trap token-bucket rate limiter. This item sets the token interval in hundredth of seconds.

avRtpQoSTrapBucketSize.name: avRtpQoSTrapBucketSize
avRtpQoSTrapBucketSize.description: Configure the QoS trap token-bucket rate limiter. This item configures the bucket-size.

avRtpDateAndTime.name: avRtpDateAndTime
avRtpDateAndTime.description: The current RTC date and Time

avRtpMaxSessionTableSize.name: avRtpMaxSessionTableSize
avRtpMaxSessionTableSize.description: The maximum number of rows of the session table

avRtpReservedSessionTableRows.name: avRtpReservedSessionTableRows
avRtpReservedSessionTableRows.description: The number of rows in session table reserved for terminated sessions that had QoS events

avRtpFaultMask.name: avRtpFaultMask
avRtpFaultMask.description: Fault mask enables Avaya Fault-Mon to poll the device status Bit 0 - Set if there is a fault condition according to avRtpQoSFaultTh/avRtpQoSClearTh

avRtpSessionTable.name: avRtpSessionTable
avRtpSessionTable.description: This table contains statistics for recently terminated RTP flows.

avRtpSessionEntry.name: avRtpSessionEntry
avRtpSessionEntry.description: Each row contains information from a single RTP session. Rows are removed when the space limits are reached (avRtpSessionTableSize). There are avRtpSessionTableReservedRows reserved rows for terminated sessions that had QoS events. Sessions that had QoS events might appear twice in the table, e.g. once with AvRtpSessionState = terminated and once with terminatedWithEvent.

avRtpSessionState.name: avRtpSessionState
avRtpSessionState.description: An arbitrary RTP-flow sequence number, serves as the MIB tables index

avRtpSessionID.name: avRtpSessionID
avRtpSessionID.description: An arbitrary RTP-flow sequence number, serves as the MIB tables index

avRtpSessionEngineID.name: avRtpSessionEngineID
avRtpSessionEngineID.description: The number of the VoIP engine responsible for the RTP stream. More information about the specific VoIP engine can be found in avRtpSumTable

avRtpSessionLocAddrType.name: avRtpSessionLocAddrType
avRtpSessionLocAddrType.description: This item specifies whether the IP addresses in this row are in IPv6 or in IPv4 format (See RFC3291)

avRtpSessionLocAddr.name: avRtpSessionLocAddr
avRtpSessionLocAddr.description: The RTP stream local RTP address.

avRtpSessionLocAddrV4.name: avRtpSessionLocAddrV4
avRtpSessionLocAddrV4.description: The RTP stream local RTP address (IPv4).

avRtpSessionLocAddrV6.name: avRtpSessionLocAddrV6
avRtpSessionLocAddrV6.description: The RTP stream local RTP address (IPv6).

avRtpSessionRemAddrType.name: avRtpSessionRemAddrType
avRtpSessionRemAddrType.description: This item specifies whether the remote IP addresses in this row is in IPv6 or in IPv4 format (See RFC3291)

avRtpSessionRemAddr.name: avRtpSessionRemAddr
avRtpSessionRemAddr.description: The RTP stream remote peer address

avRtpSessionRemAddrV4.name: avRtpSessionRemAddrV4
avRtpSessionRemAddrV4.description: The RTP stream Remote RTP address (IPv4).

avRtpSessionRemAddrV6.name: avRtpSessionRemAddrV6
avRtpSessionRemAddrV6.description: The RTP stream Remote RTP address (IPv6).

avRtpSessionLocPort.name: avRtpSessionLocPort
avRtpSessionLocPort.description: The RTP stream local UDP port

avRtpSessionRemPort.name: avRtpSessionRemPort
avRtpSessionRemPort.description: The RTP stream remote UDP port

avRtpSessionDuration.name: avRtpSessionDuration
avRtpSessionDuration.description: The duration of the stream in hundredth of seconds

avRtpSessionCname.name: avRtpSessionCname
avRtpSessionCname.description: The RTP canonical name of the gateway

avRtpSessionPhone.name: avRtpSessionPhone
avRtpSessionPhone.description: A string containing the phone extensions (received for CM), in the format of <conferenceID>:<extension #1>...<extension #N>

avRtpSessionSeverity.name: avRtpSessionSeverity
avRtpSessionSeverity.description: The QoS problem severity for the stream. This item equals to 'warning' if a trap was suppose to be sent. and 'cleared' otherwise.

avRtpSessionType.name: avRtpSessionType
avRtpSessionType.description: This value describes the session type. It holds the RTP type for RTP streams and unique items (above 127) for non-RTP or dynamically allocated types

avRtpSessionTxInterval.name: avRtpSessionTxInterval
avRtpSessionTxInterval.description: The interval (in milliseconds) between RTP packets.

avRtpSessionTxEncryp.name: avRtpSessionTxEncryp
avRtpSessionTxEncryp.description: The Media Encryption metric indicates what kind media encryption is ,if any, is used for the RTP session. This information is valuable because: 1) media-encryption consumes more VoIP resources 2) Encryption key infrastructure may cause problems encryptionOff(0) - Encryption is off encryptionAEAv2(1) - Avaya Proprietary AEAv2 encryption encryptionAES(2) - Avaya Proprietary AES encryption Standard Encryption (Secure RTP): srtpAesCm128(4) - Counter Mode 128 AES encryption, no authentication srtpAesCm128HmacSha180(5) - AES encryption, 80bit SHA1 authentication srtpAesCm128HmacSha132(6) - AES encryption, 32bit SHA1 authentication srtpF8128HmacSha180(7) - F8 encryption, 80bit SHA1 authentication srtpHmacSha180(8) - No encryption, 80bit SHA1 authentication srtpHmacSha132(9) - No encryption, 32bit SHA1 authentication

avRtpSessionTxDscp.name: avRtpSessionTxDscp
avRtpSessionTxDscp.description: The last transmitted IP DSCP. This value may change during the call according to the RSVP status.This information is valuable because routers may give different priority to packets according to their DSCP value

avRtpSessionTxVlan.name: avRtpSessionTxVlan
avRtpSessionTxVlan.description: The VLAN on which the RTP packets are transmitted. Minus one means 'unknown'

avRtpSessionTxL2Pri.name: avRtpSessionTxL2Pri
avRtpSessionTxL2Pri.description: The Layer 2 (e.g. IEEE 802.1p) priority of the sent Ethernet frames. Minus 1 means unknown. This information is valuable because Ethernet switches can give frames different priority according to their 802.1p value

avRtpSessionTxSilenceSupp.name: avRtpSessionTxSilenceSupp
avRtpSessionTxSilenceSupp.description: Silence suppression state.noRtp means that a simple silence suppression scheme was used i.e. without RTP packets on silence. Complex means that a combination of silence packets and 'no RTP on Silence' is usedThis information is valuable because: 1) silence suppression can save upto %60 bandwidth 2) Silence suppression influences user experience (especially if the terminals does not generate confort-noise)

avRtpSessionTxSsrc.name: avRtpSessionTxSsrc
avRtpSessionTxSsrc.description: The transmitted RTP stream SSRC.This value can be used to locate a stream in a packet capture.

avRtpSessionTxRsvp.name: avRtpSessionTxRsvp
avRtpSessionTxRsvp.description: The RSVP status for the stream. This information is valuable because: 1) Routers may reserve bandwidth to for the stream. 2) Avaya VoIP endpoints changes the transmitted DSCP according to the RSVP status.

avRtpSessionTxResvFail.name: avRtpSessionTxResvFail
avRtpSessionTxResvFail.description: The number of times the RSVP reservation has failed. This item is init to one if RSVP is in-use.

avRtpSessionStatInterval.name: avRtpSessionStatInterval
avRtpSessionStatInterval.description: The thresholds are evaluated periodically, usually each time an RTCP message is being sent.

avRtpSessionRxCodecPlayTime.name: avRtpSessionRxCodecPlayTime
avRtpSessionRxCodecPlayTime.description: The time the codec has played frames (not including silence suppression or fill frames)

avRtpSessionRxCodecLossCount.name: avRtpSessionRxCodecLossCount
avRtpSessionRxCodecLossCount.description: The total codec loss time in milliseconds

avRtpSessionRxCodecLoss.name: avRtpSessionRxCodecLoss
avRtpSessionRxCodecLoss.description: The codec loss during the last Statistical interval, in 1/1000 units. The codec loss is the number of fill period divided by the statistical interval. The fill period is the duration of time that the codec had to send data to the digital to analog converter, but no codec frames were available in the jitter buffer. This is a measure for the overall packet loss after the jitter and resequencing re sequencing buffers.

avRtpSessionRxAvgCodecLoss.name: avRtpSessionRxAvgCodecLoss
avRtpSessionRxAvgCodecLoss.description: The total codec loss during the session.

avRtpSessionRxCodecLossEv.name: avRtpSessionRxCodecLossEv
avRtpSessionRxCodecLossEv.description: The number of times codec loss was sampled over the threshold

avRtpSessionRxLoss.name: avRtpSessionRxLoss
avRtpSessionRxLoss.description: The received network loss in the last statistical interval (in 1/1000 units).

avRtpSessionRxAvgLoss.name: avRtpSessionRxAvgLoss
avRtpSessionRxAvgLoss.description: The total network loss during the session (in 1/1000 units).

avRtpSessionRxLossEv.name: avRtpSessionRxLossEv
avRtpSessionRxLossEv.description: The number of times network loss was sampled over the threshold

avRtpSessionRx.name: avRtpSessionRx
avRtpSessionRx.description: The total number of received RTP packets

avRtpSessionRxLossCount.name: avRtpSessionRxLossCount
avRtpSessionRxLossCount.description: The total number of lost packets

avRtpSessionRxSeqFall.name: avRtpSessionRxSeqFall
avRtpSessionRxSeqFall.description: The total number of sequence fall events

avRtpSessionRxDup.name: avRtpSessionRxDup
avRtpSessionRxDup.description: The total number of received duplicate packets. This item may indicate transient routing loop

avRtpSessionRxJBufUnderruns.name: avRtpSessionRxJBufUnderruns
avRtpSessionRxJBufUnderruns.description: The duration of jitter buffer under runs during the call in milliseconds (i.e. buffer empty when a frame is needed by the codec).

avRtpSessionRxJBufOverruns.name: avRtpSessionRxJBufOverruns
avRtpSessionRxJBufOverruns.description: The duration of time in codec frames that were dropped due to jitter buffer overruns in milliseconds (i.e. jitter buffer is full)

avRtpSessionRxJBufDelay.name: avRtpSessionRxJBufDelay
avRtpSessionRxJBufDelay.description: The last jitter buffer delay in milliseconds.

avRtpSessionRxMaxJBufDelay.name: avRtpSessionRxMaxJBufDelay
avRtpSessionRxMaxJBufDelay.description: The maximum jitter buffer delay during the call (in milliseconds)

avRtpSessionRxJitterEv.name: avRtpSessionRxJitterEv
avRtpSessionRxJitterEv.description: The number of times, jitter was sampled over the threshold.

avRtpSessionRxTtl.name: avRtpSessionRxTtl
avRtpSessionRxTtl.description: The current/last received TTL value (IP Time To Live)

avRtpSessionRxMinTtl.name: avRtpSessionRxMinTtl
avRtpSessionRxMinTtl.description: The minimum received TTL value. The technician can use this value as a hint to what was the IP route during the session.

avRtpSessionRxMaxTtl.name: avRtpSessionRxMaxTtl
avRtpSessionRxMaxTtl.description: The maximum received TTL value. Difference between this value and avRtpSessionRxMinTtl may indicate route changes during the call.

avRtpSessionRxL2Pri.name: avRtpSessionRxL2Pri
avRtpSessionRxL2Pri.description: The last received L2 priority (IEEE 802.1p, Ethernet priority)

avRtpSessionRxSsrc.name: avRtpSessionRxSsrc
avRtpSessionRxSsrc.description: The last received RTP SSRC value

avRtpSessionRxSsrcChange.name: avRtpSessionRxSsrcChange
avRtpSessionRxSsrcChange.description: Counts the number of observed SSRC changes during the call. This may indicate a remote VoIP engine fail-over event.

avRtpSessionTxRtcp.name: avRtpSessionTxRtcp
avRtpSessionTxRtcp.description: The total number of transmitted RTCP reports

avRtpSessionRxRtcp.name: avRtpSessionRxRtcp
avRtpSessionRxRtcp.description: The total number of received RTCP reports

avRtpSessionCodecRtt.name: avRtpSessionCodecRtt
avRtpSessionCodecRtt.description: The Estimated analog overall round-trip time calculated from the last received RTCP packet. The estimate value include the network delay plus the internal delays plus an estimate for the remote internal delay. This value is measured in milliseconds.

avRtpSessionAvgCodecRtt.name: avRtpSessionAvgCodecRtt
avRtpSessionAvgCodecRtt.description: The Avarage Estimated analog overall RTT (including internal delays) during the session.

avRtpSessionCodecRttEv.name: avRtpSessionCodecRttEv
avRtpSessionCodecRttEv.description: The number of times the Estimated analog codec RTT was over the threshold

avRtpSessionRtt.name: avRtpSessionRtt
avRtpSessionRtt.description: The last RTT value in milliseconds. RTT is learnt from RTCP reports

avRtpSessionAvgRtt.name: avRtpSessionAvgRtt
avRtpSessionAvgRtt.description: The average RTT during the RTP sessions

avRtpSessionRttEv.name: avRtpSessionRttEv
avRtpSessionRttEv.description: The number of received RTCP packets which has indicated that RTT was over the threshold.

avRtpSessionRemLoss.name: avRtpSessionRemLoss
avRtpSessionRemLoss.description: The last known remote loss (learnt from received RTCP message)

avRtpSessionRemAvgLoss.name: avRtpSessionRemAvgLoss
avRtpSessionRemAvgLoss.description: The last known remote loss (learnt from received RTCP message)

avRtpSessionRemLossEv.name: avRtpSessionRemLossEv
avRtpSessionRemLossEv.description: The number of received RTCP packets which has indicated that loss, at the remote peer, was over the threshold..

avRtpSessionRemJitter.name: avRtpSessionRemJitter
avRtpSessionRemJitter.description: The last known remote jitter, learnt from RTCP.

avRtpSessionRemAvgJitter.name: avRtpSessionRemAvgJitter
avRtpSessionRemAvgJitter.description: The average remote jitter, learnt from RTCP.

avRtpSessionRemJitterEv.name: avRtpSessionRemJitterEv
avRtpSessionRemJitterEv.description: The number of received RTCP messages, which have indicated that loss was over the threshold.

avRtpSessionEcTailLen.name: avRtpSessionEcTailLen
avRtpSessionEcTailLen.description: The current/last echo cancellation tail length.

avRtpSessionEcReturnLoss.name: avRtpSessionEcReturnLoss
avRtpSessionEcReturnLoss.description: The last sampled Echo Cancellation return loss.

avRtpSessionEcReturnLossEv.name: avRtpSessionEcReturnLossEv
avRtpSessionEcReturnLossEv.description: The number of time the echo cancellation return loss was sampled over the threshold. This value is sampled every avRtpSessionStatInerval

avRtpSessionAEC.name: avRtpSessionAEC
avRtpSessionAEC.description: Acoustic echo cancellation state, relevant for speaker phones

avRtpSessionDebugStr.name: avRtpSessionDebugStr
avRtpSessionDebugStr.description: This string contains the major metrics in human readable form. It is used by the QoS trap.

avRtpSumTable.name: avRtpSumTable
avRtpSumTable.description: This table contains summary of sessions and QoS events for each VoIP engine.

avRtpSumEngineID.name: avRtpSumEngineID
avRtpSumEngineID.description: VoIP engine identifier. Usually, the VoIP engine slot number.

avRtpSumEngineDescr.name: avRtpSumEngineDescr
avRtpSumEngineDescr.description: A string describing the VoIP engine. Equals to entPhysicalDescr or cmgModuleDescription

avRtpSumPeriod.name: avRtpSumPeriod
avRtpSumPeriod.description: The time since the summary counters were cleared.

avRtpSumActiveQosEvents.name: avRtpSumActiveQosEvents
avRtpSumActiveQosEvents.description: The number of flows that currently suffers from QoS problems.

avRtpSumTotalFlowsQoSEvents.name: avRtpSumTotalFlowsQoSEvents
avRtpSumTotalFlowsQoSEvents.description: The total number of flows that had QoS events

avRtpSumSessionDuration.name: avRtpSumSessionDuration
avRtpSumSessionDuration.description: Total duration of the sessions in seconds

avRtpLookupTable.name: avRtpLookupTable
avRtpLookupTable.description: This virtual table is used for finding a specific SessionIDs based on the remote address and call state.
